  					<td align=center valign="top" width=100%><br>
  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - CLERIC</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>LVL 16 TO 30 - WITHOUT WASTING TIME</font> - <small>Anonymous, Tarew Marr</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>Although alot of people say soloing makes better exp, and yes,
believe it or not, Clerics can solo. I feel that the fastest way
to lvl up is through groups. From lvls 16 to 8, I highly
recommend the oasis (just like every other character). All you
need is a tank, and you guys can destroy those crocs. It does get
a bit boring though, since all you do is meditate and cast heal
(get used to it). If you feel daring, this is your only chance to
really fight. You can fight these until lvl 18, but I suggest
once you learn your way around this zone, that you quickly get
yourslef into an orc group at the xroads (still in oasis). That
way you will have som money to purchase those new spells, and
some wisdom equipement. Don't strees out too much about wisdom
thoguh, I am currently lvl 30 whit only 140 wisdom, and it seems
suffucient (compared to a necro who would have arounf 170 int at
lvl 30).<br>
<br>
When you get to lvl 18, the experience gets very slow in the
Oasis, you can either find a tank to partner with and kill dry
bones skeletons, or goto Highhold Pass and kill orcs. I suggest
going to the pass though, since killing orcs will increase your
faction with the humans in the zone (if you are a delf - very
useful since we do not get invis). There is also reasonable loot,
you can easily make 30pp going form 18-19 with nonstop fighting
of the orcs. At lvl 19, you get your new spells, however they
arent very useful (aside form the expected hp/ac increase). At
this point I strongly recommend going to Kunark, specificaly The
Lake of Ill Omen. It ca be tuff getting there, so I suggest
either you get a port, or an escort. Once there you can easily
join a group withen the fort fighting sarnaks. The exp and loot
is amazing at this point (compared to what you should be used
to). Although a lot of group might be in their mid-20's, you can
still group with them and level up. You shouldn't have a problem
payign the 120+pp for your lvl 24 spells. Keep fighting in the
fort lvl 27. (Some people get bored fighting the sarnaks here,
but I leveled so fast that it never got to me. Also some people
try fightin by the lake, or in th goblin mines, but the exp and
loot just doesn't compare. You can also fight the different
skeletons in this zone and try out your you undead spells, but
usually groups get pissed off when you attack instead of heal, so
its almost a waste of time). Also at lvl 24, you'll get your
favorite new spell :) It's called Greater Healing - it will heal
around 240 -300 hp. Everyone will love you, and you shouldn't
have a problem ever getting into a group form now and on.<br>
<br>
At lvl 27, you can move to the next zone over and start killing
Giants in Fronteer Mountains, the exp here is equivelantly good,
and loot is varied. The Giants here drop practically no money,
but item like the forest loop will make you mad cash by
auctioning the off in the EC.<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
